  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency shelter and health assistance for IDPs in Rakhine, Myanmar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter: Emergency shelter kits will be distributed to 1,243vulnerable IDP households in the targeted displacement sites. 
Emergency Health assistance focusing on women&#x2019;s health and sexual and reproductive health rights in emergencies:Two trained mobile outreach health units comprising a community facilitator, midwife and a medical assistant will visit 10 remote displacement sites four times to provide basic check-ups focusing on pregnant and lactating women, post-delivery check-ups, provision of multi-vitamins, and assistance in referrals to hospitals based on needs. Specialised medical assistance (Obstetrics and Gynaecology) will be provided twice to women and adolescent girls as a part of the outreach health unit&#x2019;s work. Approximately 3,140 women will receive primary health care support.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The emergency shelter needs of 1,243 highly vulnerable IDP HHs in displacement sites are met.
Increased access to essential emergency health care and medical services for crisis-affected people through outreach health units</narrative>
  </description>
